<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple HTML with CSS Classes</title>
    <!-- Internal CSS -->
    <style>
        .header {
            background-color: lightblue;
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .title {
            font-size: 2em;
            color: darkblue;
        }

        .paragraph {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            color: #333;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        .button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: green;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .button:hover {
            background-color: darkgreen;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header class="header">
        <h1 class="title">Welcome to My Simple Webpage</h1>
    </header>

    <p class="paragraph">
        This is a simple paragraph styled using a class selector. You can easily customize the style with CSS.
    </p>

    <p class="paragraph">
        CSS allows you to control the appearance of elements on your web page. Try changing the values in the style section to see the difference!
    </p>

    <button class="button">Click Me</button>

